message: I am working in Congress to ensure this doesn’t happen again. The House-passed #NDAA would require the consent of the mayor for out-of-state National Guard troops to be deployed in DC and my own bill would give the mayor control of the DC National Guard. https://t.co/CZjv6zuXYR

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: This @WashingtonPost investigation found that Trump deployed 3,800 troops from around the nation to DC. “Trump…drew on the President’s little-known role as commander in chief of the D.C. National Guard, akin to that of a governor in a state, to facilitate the deployment.”

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: In a moment no #DC resident will ever forget, this summer #Trump called National Guard troops from around the nation to fill our city’s streets in an empty show of force, ignoring DC’s will and suppressing the voices of peaceful protestors.

message:

message:
"The Latin American Youth Center around for 52 years. We provide a holistic approach, wrap-around services, and serve about 5,000 youths annually."

--Lupi Quinteros-Grady, @THELAYC

message:
"Short term, we've been triaging with our small business owners, helping them pivot quickly to new ways to do business."

--Marla Bilonick, @LEDCMetro

message: "We're teaching our constituents how to register online, so it's very easy, and it's in Spanish. It's bilingual. We make it as easy as possible to vote, but also to be counted in the #2020Census." -- Director Jackie Reyes-Yanes, @OLADCGov

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: Danny Friedman from @VotoLatino has more than a decade of experience in political advocacy. I'm pleased to turn it over to Danny at this time.

message: "#DC has same-day registration, so if you miss the deadline, you can register on the day you vote this year." -- Karla Garcia, @Vote4DC

message: Yesterday’s revelations further expose the hypocrisy of the man who currently holds the highest office in the country.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: #DC residents pay the highest taxes per capita, yet President #Trump has repeatedly attacked the idea that the residents of our nation’s capital deserve a vote in Congress.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: At its core, the argument for D.C. statehood, which overwhelmingly passed in the House of Representatives in June, is the rallying cry of the Revolutionary War: #NoTaxationWithoutRepresentation.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: The news about President Trump’s taxes yesterday – he paid a total of $750 in federal income taxes during his first year in office despite repeatedly bragging that he is a billionaire – makes his attacks on #DCStatehood even more outrageous.

message: By holding this hearing today, we ensure that the DBE program and the business owners it lifts up receive thorough consideration by this Committee.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: This program, when properly administered and enforced, ensures that businesses owned by women and minorities have a fair chance to compete for federally assisted transportation contracts.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: One of the most powerful tools in the field of transportation and construction to assist people who have routinely been left out or left behind is the U.S. Department of Transportation’s Disadvantaged Business Enterprise (DBE) Program.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: I've spent my entire career - in Congress, and as Chair of the @USEEOC before that - fighting for equality and seeking to break down barriers so that truly all citizens have the same opportunities to participate and thrive in our economy and our society.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: Over the last few months, the vulnerability of people of color has been unmistakably demonstrated as we ride wave after wave of crisis – a global pandemic, a tanking economy, and systemic racism repeatedly manifesting as physical violence.

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: We are at a pivotal moment in our Nation’s history. We are shining a long overdue light on the lived realities for people of color in this country, despite our pledge of “liberty and justice for all.”

name: Norton, Eleanor Holmes
message: Thank you, Chair @RepPeterDeFazio, for holding this important hearing. Today presents a welcome opportunity to elevate the realities of minority and women-owned business owners.
